The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, October 14, 2003 				 Packet tea enlivens Tatas
 OUR CORRESPONDENT 																								New Delhi, Oct. 13: Tata Tea, with a 7.4 per cent market share in packaged tea in India, has shown a double digit growth ever since the brand was re-launched last year.																								Speaking at the launch of Tata Tea Gold, a premium blended tea, managing director Percy Siganporia said, At a time when packaged tea market is showing a dismal performance, Tata Tea has grown 7.4 per cent in terms of value and 8.8 per cent in terms of volume since the brand was re-launched last year. 																								Tata Tea Gold has been priced at Rs 45 for a 250-gm packet and Rs 90 for 500 gms. In terms of pricing, it is close to Tata Tea Premium brand, which is priced at Rs 42.50 for a 250-gram pack. 																								The USP of Tata Tea Gold will be its blending, which is 85 per cent CTC and 15 per cent long-leaf tea, said a spokesperson for the company.																								The other products, spread across premium, economy and popular categories, include Agni, Kanan Devan, Gemini, Chakra Gold and Tetley International blend. 
